1
00:00:10,271 --> 00:00:11,604
[PA chiming]

2
00:00:11,687 --> 00:00:13,729
[woman on PA] May I have your attention,
please.

3
00:00:13,812 --> 00:00:19,562
Baggage from flight TX-551 is now arriving
from Fort-de-France at carousel four.

4
00:00:19,646 --> 00:00:24,771
Again, baggage from flight TX-551
is arriving at carousel four.

5
00:00:36,104 --> 00:00:40,479
For security reasons, please keep
your belongings within sight at all times.

6
00:00:40,562 --> 00:00:41,771
CUSTOMS & INDIRECT TAXES

7
00:00:41,854 --> 00:00:44,146
Any unclaimed baggage
will be confiscated and destroyed.

8
00:00:44,229 --> 00:00:46,604
Thank you for your compliance.

9
00:00:52,104 --> 00:00:53,812
Ma'am, bag inspection.

10
00:00:53,896 --> 00:00:56,146
Place your suitcases
on the belt here, please.

11
00:00:57,271 --> 00:00:59,687
- You coming in from…
- Martinique.

12
00:01:00,646 --> 00:01:01,646
Anything to declare?

13
00:01:03,187 --> 00:01:04,979
- Huh?
- Any plants or computer equipment

14
00:01:05,062 --> 00:01:06,562
exceeding the authorized quantity?

15
00:01:07,604 --> 00:01:09,687
- Everything in order?
- No. Yes.

16
00:01:10,854 --> 00:01:11,854
Yes? No?

17
00:01:11,937 --> 00:01:13,354
Nothing to declare.

18
00:01:27,021 --> 00:01:30,021
[tense music playing]

19
00:01:36,521 --> 00:01:38,021
Over here, ma'am.

20
00:01:40,437 --> 00:01:42,187
Open your suitcase, please.

21
00:01:47,562 --> 00:01:49,562
[tense music continues]

22
00:01:52,021 --> 00:01:54,312
[suitcase unzipping]

23
00:02:19,521 --> 00:02:21,062
[dog barking]

24
00:02:21,146 --> 00:02:23,437
[tense music building]

25
00:02:28,854 --> 00:02:30,604
- [man] Go on.
- [woman] Find. Find.

26
00:02:32,812 --> 00:02:33,854
[man] Find.

27
00:02:34,437 --> 00:02:37,604
[woman] Go on. Search.
Look. Good boy. Here, too.

28
00:02:38,812 --> 00:02:41,312
Find. That's it. Find.

29
00:02:42,521 --> 00:02:45,604
Stop. Stop. Not that.
Stop. Stop. Give it here.

30
00:02:45,687 --> 00:02:47,396
Drop it. Drop it. Stop.

31
00:02:47,479 --> 00:02:49,604
- [man] Hey, Rafale. Let's go.
- [dog whines and yips]

32
00:02:50,437 --> 00:02:51,896
Sorry for the inconvenience, ma'am.

33
00:02:56,896 --> 00:02:58,896
[tense music fading]

34
00:03:02,896 --> 00:03:04,896
[indistinct chatter]

35
00:03:17,687 --> 00:03:20,312
- [recording chimes]
- Made it through.

36
00:03:27,604 --> 00:03:28,771
Annabelle?

37
00:03:29,937 --> 00:03:31,312
Whatever goes down, I've got you.

38
00:03:33,354 --> 00:03:35,104
Through blood, life is never happenstance.

39
00:03:36,104 --> 00:03:37,646
- Xhésus.
- I'm sorry?

40
00:03:37,729 --> 00:03:40,396
Xhésus. Think "Jesus," but with a "xh."

41
00:03:41,521 --> 00:03:42,354
Forget it.

42
00:03:44,771 --> 00:03:46,771
No, no, I'm fine. I've got it.

43
00:03:47,979 --> 00:03:48,979
This way.

44
00:04:03,229 --> 00:04:04,687
Let me. I've got it.

45
00:04:50,646 --> 00:04:51,646
[door closes]

46
00:05:02,312 --> 00:05:03,312
Hungry?

47
00:05:27,312 --> 00:05:33,771
WE'RE AT THE HOTEL,
IS THAT NORMAL?

48
00:05:42,687 --> 00:05:44,021
[clicks tongue]

49
00:05:44,562 --> 00:05:45,979
[Xhésus] I left, I'm sorry.

50
00:05:46,062 --> 00:05:49,396
Didn't want to wake you.
I had a last-minute errand to run.

51
00:05:50,187 --> 00:05:52,729
Yeah, of course.
Want me to bring you some?

52
00:05:53,521 --> 00:05:56,479
No worries. I'll let you go, I'm at work.

53
00:05:57,229 --> 00:05:58,312
Me too, Mom.

54
00:06:00,729 --> 00:06:03,146
- [laughs softly] Sorry.
- No worries.

55
00:06:03,229 --> 00:06:05,312
Gotta stop by the pharmacy
or I'll just forget again.

56
00:06:06,021 --> 00:06:08,479
So, how does this thing work?

57
00:06:08,562 --> 00:06:12,187
We can take care of business now,
or if you want, we can grab a bite first.

58
00:06:12,271 --> 00:06:13,437
Your pick.

59
00:06:14,146 --> 00:06:15,271
My treat.

60
00:06:17,271 --> 00:06:19,271
[indistinct hushed chatter]

61
00:06:25,937 --> 00:06:27,937
[Xhésus] To be honest, I'm impressed.

62
00:06:28,021 --> 00:06:29,437
Hiding the stash.

63
00:06:30,021 --> 00:06:33,312
I didn't believe you'd pull it off,
but not bad.

64
00:06:34,271 --> 00:06:35,437
How'd you manage?

65
00:06:36,229 --> 00:06:38,104
Got someone on the inside?

66
00:06:38,187 --> 00:06:39,396
Inside what?

67
00:06:39,896 --> 00:06:41,021
[laughs softly]

68
00:06:45,229 --> 00:06:46,354
Gimme a sec.

69
00:06:46,437 --> 00:06:48,854
Gotta call my mother
and tell her I picked up her medicine.

70
00:06:48,937 --> 00:06:50,771
Okay, no worries.

71
00:06:51,312 --> 00:06:52,896
- Is she sick?
- No.

72
00:06:52,979 --> 00:06:54,646
[chuckles] Hypochondriac.

73
00:06:55,312 --> 00:06:56,146
[laughs softly]

74
00:07:16,646 --> 00:07:18,479
[phone vibrating]

75
00:07:20,562 --> 00:07:22,646
KING
If you're with Jesus it's all good.

76
00:07:29,479 --> 00:07:33,562
Résus. Yes I'm with him.

77
00:07:33,646 --> 00:07:36,646
["Destinée" by Yaniss Odua playing]

78
00:07:39,771 --> 00:07:40,771
[bell dings]

79
00:07:46,021 --> 00:07:48,354
- Ah, Kingsley.
- How are you, Auntie?

80
00:07:48,437 --> 00:07:49,562
Fine, and you?

81
00:07:49,646 --> 00:07:50,646
The monsters here?

82
00:07:50,729 --> 00:07:52,771
- Well, yes, but they're about to--
- Just popping in.

83
00:07:52,854 --> 00:07:54,104
Kingsley!

84
00:07:54,187 --> 00:07:57,146
What up, champ? Mmm! Whoa, whoa, whoa.

85
00:07:57,229 --> 00:07:59,812
[chuckles] You've put on muscle!

86
00:07:59,896 --> 00:08:01,521
I won't be able to pick you up soon.

87
00:08:01,604 --> 00:08:03,479
- [laughs]
- [Nolan] King!

88
00:08:03,562 --> 00:08:05,062
[Kingsley] Hey, little buddy!

89
00:08:07,271 --> 00:08:09,604
- [Thaïs] King!
- [Kingsley chuckling]

90
00:08:14,479 --> 00:08:17,271
Come on. I've got a surprise.

91
00:08:29,187 --> 00:08:30,896
Hmm, hmm.

92
00:08:33,271 --> 00:08:34,396
It's a'ight.

93
00:08:37,271 --> 00:08:39,312
Hmm. Not very soft.

94
00:08:41,271 --> 00:08:42,187
Hmm.

95
00:08:44,521 --> 00:08:45,687
Hmm.

96
00:08:47,187 --> 00:08:48,354
Check this out.

97
00:08:57,937 --> 00:09:00,146
- Cool or what?
- [Nolan] Mmm.

98
00:09:02,271 --> 00:09:03,479
That's so cool.

99
00:09:03,562 --> 00:09:07,312
Pick one, and when you're home,
that's what will be waiting for you.

100
00:09:07,396 --> 00:09:09,062
And when is that?

101
00:09:09,146 --> 00:09:10,604
- Soon.
- But how soon?

102
00:09:10,687 --> 00:09:14,646
When you count to 878,456.

103
00:09:14,729 --> 00:09:16,062
- That's not fair!
- [laughs]

104
00:09:16,979 --> 00:09:18,146
Wow.

105
00:09:18,229 --> 00:09:20,021
- [Mathis] Hey, King.
- Hmm?

106
00:09:20,104 --> 00:09:21,562
Have you seen Léo?

107
00:09:22,062 --> 00:09:24,354
- What?
- Have you seen his video?

108
00:09:24,437 --> 00:09:26,979
What video?
Wait, when did you guys get phones?

109
00:09:27,604 --> 00:09:30,146
No, Auntie Régine showed us the video.

110
00:09:30,229 --> 00:09:33,937
She yelled at us,
said we were all just a bunch of punks.

111
00:09:36,187 --> 00:09:39,479
Whoa.
Check it out, that desk is so pretty.

112
00:09:39,562 --> 00:09:40,729
Look at that bed there.

113
00:09:40,812 --> 00:09:44,271
[Léo on video] I shot that asshole
in his face! Boom!

114
00:09:44,354 --> 00:09:47,021
- In his mouth! For real!
- Damn, what a dumbass!

115
00:09:47,104 --> 00:09:49,187
I ride for my fam, understood?

116
00:09:49,271 --> 00:09:51,896
- I'm armed, so don't fuck around, fuckers.
- [clicks tongue]

117
00:10:08,104 --> 00:10:11,229
- [woman] Jérôme? Come look at this.
- No, Mama, I don't have time.

118
00:10:11,312 --> 00:10:13,729
Oh no?
What do you mean, you don't have time?

119
00:10:13,812 --> 00:10:15,271
Come look at this now.

120
00:10:15,354 --> 00:10:16,354
What is it?

121
00:10:18,854 --> 00:10:22,229
I told you before not to bring any kids
into your damn affairs.

122
00:10:22,312 --> 00:10:25,021
Come on, Mama. You know I'm better
than to do something like that.

123
00:10:25,104 --> 00:10:27,479
Yeah? Then explain this.

124
00:10:30,604 --> 00:10:32,771
[Léo on video] I shot that asshole
in his face!

125
00:10:33,354 --> 00:10:34,562
Boom!

126
00:10:34,646 --> 00:10:36,562
In his mouth! For real!

127
00:10:37,562 --> 00:10:39,562
I ride for my fam, understood?

128
00:10:39,646 --> 00:10:42,771
I'm armed, so don't fuck around, fuckers.

129
00:10:42,854 --> 00:10:44,229
We're inadmissible.

130
00:10:44,729 --> 00:10:46,896
[imitates gun firing]

131
00:10:49,896 --> 00:10:51,604
What is this supposed to be, Mama?

132
00:10:51,687 --> 00:10:54,062
- It's what you do!
- [SherKhan clicks tongue]

133
00:10:56,229 --> 00:10:57,687
This money's what we do.

134
00:11:07,771 --> 00:11:10,146
I don't interfere in your business, son.

135
00:11:11,521 --> 00:11:13,521
But you better
leave the kids out of it, Jérôme.

136
00:11:13,604 --> 00:11:15,354
And especially if guns are involved.

137
00:11:15,437 --> 00:11:17,604
When it comes to the kids,
you're forbidden.

138
00:11:17,687 --> 00:11:20,271
Mama, I don't have guns.
I have no idea what that is.

139
00:11:20,354 --> 00:11:21,521
Yes, you do.

140
00:11:21,604 --> 00:11:24,146
He's a Lafleur, one of Marilyn's.

141
00:11:24,229 --> 00:11:26,521
She sold plants at the local market.

142
00:11:26,604 --> 00:11:28,521
We went to her funeral, me and your Mama.

143
00:11:28,604 --> 00:11:30,104
[dark music playing]

144
00:11:39,896 --> 00:11:40,896
NEW MESSAGE

145
00:11:42,521 --> 00:11:44,646
- Where they from?
- Saint-Joseph.

146
00:11:50,354 --> 00:11:53,312
[woman] Jérôme! Have you eaten?

147
00:11:53,396 --> 00:11:54,396
Jérôme!

148
00:11:54,479 --> 00:11:57,479
[darkly intriguing music playing]

149
00:12:01,104 --> 00:12:03,271
[Léo on video] Boom! In his mouth!

150
00:12:03,354 --> 00:12:04,229
For real!

151
00:12:04,312 --> 00:12:06,187
I ride for my fam, understood?

152
00:12:06,271 --> 00:12:09,354
I'm armed, so don't fuck around, fuckers.

153
00:12:09,437 --> 00:12:10,687
We're inadmissible.

154
00:12:14,187 --> 00:12:17,187
[darkly intriguing music continues]

155
00:12:27,271 --> 00:12:29,271
[music fades]

156
00:12:32,312 --> 00:12:34,021
The smell bother you?

157
00:12:34,104 --> 00:12:35,271
It's fine.

158
00:12:38,354 --> 00:12:40,604
We need a deposit first, 10%.

159
00:12:41,729 --> 00:12:42,937
Sixty grand?

160
00:12:43,021 --> 00:12:45,312
Sixty-four. Don't cheap out.

161
00:12:46,812 --> 00:12:47,896
When?

162
00:12:47,979 --> 00:12:49,187
Tomorrow.

163
00:12:52,521 --> 00:12:53,729
Got a problem?

164
00:12:54,396 --> 00:12:55,396
No.

165
00:12:56,312 --> 00:12:57,562
Better not.

166
00:12:58,062 --> 00:13:02,021
The Señora doesn't take bad news well,
if you know what I'm saying.

167
00:13:03,896 --> 00:13:05,646
So don't mess this up.

168
00:13:05,729 --> 00:13:08,979
Be on time, be reliable, never default.

169
00:13:09,062 --> 00:13:11,021
The more she loves,
the more she chastises.

170
00:13:12,146 --> 00:13:14,479
You have no idea
the number of friends she's cut down

171
00:13:14,562 --> 00:13:16,104
just for standing up to her.

172
00:13:19,437 --> 00:13:22,604
I mixed up my left and my right
when giving her directions once.

173
00:13:24,687 --> 00:13:26,104
[sighs] I got it.

174
00:13:26,187 --> 00:13:27,271
[clears throat]

175
00:13:28,021 --> 00:13:29,896
- [sizzling]
- [Kylian groaning]

176
00:13:38,312 --> 00:13:39,729
What the fuck?

177
00:13:40,229 --> 00:13:42,104
I like marking my territory.

178
00:13:42,937 --> 00:13:44,104
All right, get out.

179
00:13:44,687 --> 00:13:46,562
I'll send you
the coordinates for next time.

180
00:13:51,812 --> 00:13:53,812
[indistinct chatter]

181
00:14:05,104 --> 00:14:07,104
[scooter rides off]

182
00:14:12,312 --> 00:14:14,312
[chatter continues]

183
00:14:14,396 --> 00:14:17,271
Kiki? What you doing here?

184
00:14:18,229 --> 00:14:19,354
What about you?

185
00:14:19,854 --> 00:14:21,812
You see that little idiot's video?

186
00:14:22,979 --> 00:14:24,562
I'm gonna break his teeth.

187
00:14:25,062 --> 00:14:27,896
SherKhan will figure it out.
He's gonna be like a bloodhound on you.

188
00:14:27,979 --> 00:14:31,229
It's just a dumb video on TikTok.
Let's not go nuts.

189
00:14:31,812 --> 00:14:33,312
What you up to here?

190
00:14:41,062 --> 00:14:42,521
What, you get burned?

191
00:14:43,479 --> 00:14:44,979
It's nothing, don't worry.

192
00:14:51,646 --> 00:14:53,229
How's it going, dude?

193
00:14:53,312 --> 00:14:54,812
- Hey, gimme your phone.
- Hey!

194
00:14:54,896 --> 00:14:57,146
- Now.
- I don't have it. I don't have it.

195
00:14:58,937 --> 00:15:00,771
Hey, gimme that!

196
00:15:04,021 --> 00:15:05,521
Log in now and wipe your account.

197
00:15:05,604 --> 00:15:07,187
What? Hell no, you crazy!

198
00:15:07,271 --> 00:15:10,812
Hey! Do it now or I'm sending you
to live with Auntie Régine.

199
00:15:10,896 --> 00:15:12,312
I'll talk to the judge.

200
00:15:13,562 --> 00:15:14,562
[Léo scoffs]

201
00:15:14,646 --> 00:15:17,021
[Kylian] You understand
the problem this caused?

202
00:15:17,104 --> 00:15:19,271
King brought you on to the team,
he trusted you,

203
00:15:19,354 --> 00:15:21,937
and you're blasting your face
all over the internet.

204
00:15:22,021 --> 00:15:25,271
- Because of you, King here is a dead man.
- No, please don't say that!

205
00:15:25,354 --> 00:15:27,562
He is. He'll be killed and so will you.

206
00:15:28,062 --> 00:15:28,896
No.

207
00:15:28,979 --> 00:15:30,021
Yes.

208
00:15:30,104 --> 00:15:33,062
It's too late for King.
He'll be killed cause of you.

209
00:15:33,146 --> 00:15:35,729
Thaïs, Nolan, Mathis,
they'll never come home again.

210
00:15:35,812 --> 00:15:38,396
Because we'll be a family of bandits.
You hear me?

211
00:15:39,812 --> 00:15:41,729
You're gonna have
to watch your back from now on.

212
00:15:41,812 --> 00:15:44,021
- All right.
- No way, man. It's better he know.

213
00:15:44,104 --> 00:15:46,521
You're going overboard now. It's good.

214
00:15:46,604 --> 00:15:49,687
- [bell ringing]
- Go on, get. We'll talk later.

215
00:15:54,479 --> 00:15:57,229
Well, have fun?

216
00:16:00,021 --> 00:16:02,021
[poignant music playing]

217
00:16:03,729 --> 00:16:04,979
And Annabelle?

218
00:16:06,562 --> 00:16:08,687
It's going. We're almost there.

219
00:16:08,771 --> 00:16:09,771
Okay.

220
00:16:10,271 --> 00:16:11,854
Thank you, bro.

221
00:16:11,937 --> 00:16:13,937
I feel less alone. Appreciate it.

222
00:16:17,062 --> 00:16:20,312
[poignant music continues]

223
00:16:33,437 --> 00:16:35,687
- [both laughing]
- [Xhésus] Complete nightmare.

224
00:16:35,771 --> 00:16:37,229
Yeah, that's not cool.

225
00:16:39,562 --> 00:16:41,312
Time to get to work.

226
00:17:08,354 --> 00:17:09,562
[Annabelle] There.

227
00:17:22,104 --> 00:17:23,104
Very clever.

228
00:17:38,646 --> 00:17:39,896
Where's the cash?

229
00:17:40,729 --> 00:17:41,812
Don't have it on me.

230
00:17:42,437 --> 00:17:44,021
First, I take these to my guys.

231
00:17:44,104 --> 00:17:47,437
We test each bag, and if it's all good,
I come back with the money.

232
00:17:48,146 --> 00:17:49,812
Mmm-mmm. I'm sorry, but no.

233
00:17:49,896 --> 00:17:52,562
- What do you think this was?
- I don't know.

234
00:17:53,271 --> 00:17:54,437
Can you test them here?

235
00:17:55,104 --> 00:17:57,729
Need machines for that.
You know, equipment and shit.

236
00:17:58,229 --> 00:18:01,271
I never touch cocaine.
I'm in the dark. I just smoke.

237
00:18:03,062 --> 00:18:04,187
And you?

238
00:18:05,021 --> 00:18:06,104
Same.

239
00:18:16,687 --> 00:18:18,812
- Thanks.
- I'll be back in a few hours.

240
00:18:20,146 --> 00:18:21,354
Have some fun.

241
00:18:21,437 --> 00:18:23,146
There's a pool, a spa.

242
00:18:25,062 --> 00:18:26,854
You can book a massage if you want.

243
00:18:30,646 --> 00:18:32,062
Can I have your number?

244
00:18:33,687 --> 00:18:34,687
Of course.

245
00:18:35,687 --> 00:18:41,604
06-39-98-23-54.

246
00:18:43,646 --> 00:18:46,187
- [phone ringing]
- [laughs softly]

247
00:18:49,396 --> 00:18:50,646
- Hello?
- [voice echoes]

248
00:18:52,396 --> 00:18:54,187
Don't worry about it. I get it.

249
00:18:57,854 --> 00:18:58,896
Later.

250
00:18:59,562 --> 00:19:00,937
[door opens]

251
00:19:03,437 --> 00:19:04,562
[door closes]

252
00:19:05,771 --> 00:19:07,771
DUCOS PENITENTIARY

253
00:19:12,104 --> 00:19:15,437
You want half of what I earn
when we can barely afford food?

254
00:19:15,521 --> 00:19:18,271
You think I'm the dumb one?
That I'm not up to speed?

255
00:19:19,521 --> 00:19:23,187
Those little idiots might think
you're a saint with your lotus ring,

256
00:19:23,271 --> 00:19:25,854
but that don't work on me, okay?

257
00:19:25,937 --> 00:19:28,604
Your dumb ass is out there
bragging about getting all that dough.

258
00:19:28,687 --> 00:19:29,771
I haven't done shit.

259
00:19:29,854 --> 00:19:32,021
You will, though, son. I know you.

260
00:19:33,687 --> 00:19:36,312
But it makes me happy
that you would still tell me the truth.

261
00:19:36,396 --> 00:19:38,187
It means that you and I
are still connected.

262
00:19:38,979 --> 00:19:40,396
You know I came for help.

263
00:19:40,479 --> 00:19:43,229
This is how you respond?
By threatening my family?

264
00:19:43,312 --> 00:19:44,562
Your family?

265
00:19:45,062 --> 00:19:46,562
And me, I'm not your family?

266
00:19:48,562 --> 00:19:49,937
Ah, your real family.

267
00:19:50,021 --> 00:19:53,062
But if I'm not your family,
get out of here!

268
00:19:53,562 --> 00:19:56,062
Get the fuck out, boy.
You better not come back, I'm serious.

269
00:19:56,146 --> 00:19:57,396
Beat it!

270
00:19:59,062 --> 00:20:00,729
[chair scrapes]

271
00:20:03,146 --> 00:20:04,354
Wait.

272
00:20:05,021 --> 00:20:07,146
Sit down, son. Come on.
Sit down. Sit down.

273
00:20:11,187 --> 00:20:12,937
Don't push me away.

274
00:20:13,021 --> 00:20:17,146
I wasn't there for you, but I'm sure
I'm not the first dad to do wrong.

275
00:20:17,229 --> 00:20:20,229
Give me a chance. I'm begging you, son.

276
00:20:22,979 --> 00:20:24,021
Don't ever send Jocelyn.

277
00:20:25,521 --> 00:20:27,312
Just cut me into the business.

278
00:20:27,812 --> 00:20:30,229
50%? Are you mad?

279
00:20:30,312 --> 00:20:31,812
Okay, 40%.

280
00:20:31,896 --> 00:20:33,979
Why? You don't deserve to get anything!

281
00:20:34,062 --> 00:20:36,062
Because you're my son.

282
00:20:39,521 --> 00:20:40,771
You know…

283
00:20:42,021 --> 00:20:44,021
I've only got one photo…

284
00:20:44,604 --> 00:20:45,771
in my cell.

285
00:20:46,271 --> 00:20:47,521
It's of you.

286
00:20:48,771 --> 00:20:50,021
Here, look.

287
00:20:55,437 --> 00:20:57,354
[pensive music playing]

288
00:21:01,521 --> 00:21:02,687
With Dylan.

289
00:21:04,229 --> 00:21:06,104
It's the only one I have.

290
00:21:13,687 --> 00:21:15,229
Don't let me go, son.

291
00:21:21,312 --> 00:21:22,646
Let me think it over.

292
00:21:24,062 --> 00:21:25,396
Okay, think on it.

293
00:21:26,271 --> 00:21:27,896
Hold on to the photo.

294
00:21:31,312 --> 00:21:33,312
[pensive music continues]

295
00:21:46,229 --> 00:21:49,229
- [pensive music building]
- [cell door buzzes]

296
00:21:54,646 --> 00:21:56,646
[pensive music continues]

297
00:22:34,396 --> 00:22:37,396
["Fix Dem" by Niko & DJ Digital playing]

298
00:22:40,396 --> 00:22:43,854
SIX YEARS EARLIER

299
00:22:57,396 --> 00:22:58,437
Matthew!

300
00:22:58,937 --> 00:22:59,979
Was this you?

301
00:23:00,812 --> 00:23:02,937
- Matthew!
- Kylian, they did this on you?

302
00:23:03,021 --> 00:23:04,021
Yes.

303
00:23:05,729 --> 00:23:08,979
Hey, my brother didn't do this.

304
00:23:09,979 --> 00:23:11,021
Get lost.

305
00:23:11,104 --> 00:23:12,146
[grunts]

306
00:23:15,187 --> 00:23:16,312
[groaning]

307
00:23:19,396 --> 00:23:20,521
Ahh!

308
00:23:21,396 --> 00:23:24,646
[panting] Now you better
go tell your mother who beat you!

309
00:23:26,437 --> 00:23:28,437
["Fix Dem" continues playing]

310
00:23:37,854 --> 00:23:40,146
You let it slide, game over.

311
00:23:40,646 --> 00:23:44,646
Teach them a lesson for what they did,
what they're doing, and what they will do.

312
00:23:44,729 --> 00:23:45,812
[Kylian] Yeah.

313
00:23:46,729 --> 00:23:49,187
Never let anybody think they're above you.

314
00:23:49,271 --> 00:23:50,396
Never.

315
00:23:50,479 --> 00:23:52,604
If they do, they gotta pay.

316
00:23:54,104 --> 00:23:55,437
[Marilyn] Dinner time!

317
00:23:57,146 --> 00:23:59,562
No, guys. We can't move this way.

318
00:23:59,646 --> 00:24:03,062
They're waiting.
Gotta trap them from behind.

319
00:24:03,646 --> 00:24:04,937
Ambre?

320
00:24:05,021 --> 00:24:07,104
- What?
- He can't get out.

321
00:24:07,187 --> 00:24:09,646
- [Marilyn] Dinner!
- Shh. You're distracting him.

322
00:24:10,521 --> 00:24:13,062
Gotta make them think
we're coming from the opposite side!

323
00:24:13,146 --> 00:24:14,396
How come?

324
00:24:14,479 --> 00:24:16,604
You dumb? He's not talking to us.

325
00:24:17,937 --> 00:24:19,854
How come you're all still in here?

326
00:24:19,937 --> 00:24:22,687
Dylan, you spend way too much time
on that computer.

327
00:24:22,771 --> 00:24:24,896
[Dylan] No, Mama! No!

328
00:24:24,979 --> 00:24:26,479
Come eat!

329
00:24:29,687 --> 00:24:31,271
Who's Milord?

330
00:24:31,354 --> 00:24:32,812
It's Dylan, idiot.

331
00:24:32,896 --> 00:24:34,854
But why are you called "Milord"?

332
00:24:40,437 --> 00:24:42,479
Milord means you come from a high place.

333
00:24:42,562 --> 00:24:44,062
High what?

334
00:24:44,146 --> 00:24:45,437
High society.

335
00:24:45,521 --> 00:24:47,021
You're at the very top.

336
00:24:47,104 --> 00:24:49,271
There's no one else above you.

337
00:24:50,646 --> 00:24:53,521
[determined music playing]

338
00:25:19,312 --> 00:25:22,354
Hey, Kylian Lafleur.
Who's gonna protect you now, huh?

339
00:25:22,437 --> 00:25:23,729
Stop!

340
00:25:28,646 --> 00:25:31,187
Let me go! Let me go!

341
00:25:33,687 --> 00:25:35,146
- [kid laughing]
- [slaps]

342
00:25:35,229 --> 00:25:38,521
The wild pigs are gonna eat you up
till there's nothing left.

343
00:25:41,021 --> 00:25:43,021
Anyone!

344
00:25:44,021 --> 00:25:45,062
Over here!

345
00:25:45,146 --> 00:25:47,146
Someone help!

346
00:25:47,937 --> 00:25:49,646
Help me!

347
00:25:50,604 --> 00:25:52,604
[determined music continues]

348
00:25:55,312 --> 00:25:57,312
[bird screeching]

349
00:26:03,062 --> 00:26:04,229
Mama?

350
00:26:05,937 --> 00:26:07,146
[bird screeches]

351
00:26:14,354 --> 00:26:15,771
- [pig squeals]
- [gasps]

352
00:26:15,854 --> 00:26:17,854
[squealing continues]

353
00:26:24,021 --> 00:26:26,229
[tapping] Hey, little man.

354
00:26:26,312 --> 00:26:27,479
You okay?

355
00:26:29,104 --> 00:26:30,229
Buddy?

356
00:26:32,062 --> 00:26:33,562
[music fades]

357
00:26:45,521 --> 00:26:47,521
[man 1 on TV] Good things
get out of control.

358
00:26:47,604 --> 00:26:50,979
We've created a monster
that's putting us all out of jobs,

359
00:26:51,062 --> 00:26:52,437
and I'll tell you…

360
00:26:52,521 --> 00:26:54,187
[man 2] All right, Ed, I'll be serious.

361
00:26:54,271 --> 00:26:55,896
As old Abe Martin used to say,

362
00:26:55,979 --> 00:26:59,104
it's amazing how a few facts
will break up an argument.

363
00:26:59,604 --> 00:27:03,104
[man 1] The trouble is
a lot of us don't get the whole picture.

364
00:27:03,187 --> 00:27:05,021
[man 2] You know,
I wish you had been with me

365
00:27:05,104 --> 00:27:07,312
at the workshop of an old friend
the other afternoon.

366
00:27:08,396 --> 00:27:11,187
[automated voice] The number
you have dialed is not in service.

367
00:27:11,271 --> 00:27:13,854
Please check the number and try again.

368
00:27:13,937 --> 00:27:15,021
[phone beeps]

369
00:27:18,521 --> 00:27:21,021
- The number you have dialed--
- That asshole!

370
00:27:22,271 --> 00:27:25,854
[suspenseful music playing]

371
00:27:30,479 --> 00:27:33,896
You're all set, sir. Room 430.

372
00:27:33,979 --> 00:27:36,896
Your luggage
has already been moved to your room.

373
00:27:36,979 --> 00:27:38,354
Elevators are on the right.

374
00:27:38,437 --> 00:27:39,479
- Fourth floor.
- Thank you.

375
00:27:39,562 --> 00:27:42,604
Excuse me, do you have the number
of the man who reserved my room, please?

376
00:27:42,687 --> 00:27:44,396
Uh, which room would that be, ma'am?

377
00:27:46,021 --> 00:27:49,646
It's on the fifth floor.
Way back, at the end of the hall.

378
00:27:49,729 --> 00:27:51,271
On the right, next to the elevator.

379
00:27:51,937 --> 00:27:52,937
502?

380
00:27:53,687 --> 00:27:55,937
- Yes.
- Do you have your key card?

381
00:27:56,021 --> 00:27:57,021
Key card?

382
00:27:57,104 --> 00:27:59,562
- Uh, are you sure that--
- Yes, I'm sure! God damn it!

383
00:28:00,896 --> 00:28:02,062
[Annabelle huffs]

384
00:28:07,812 --> 00:28:09,646
I have it! Here! Here!

385
00:28:09,729 --> 00:28:10,729
Here, here!

386
00:28:13,396 --> 00:28:14,854
[typing]

387
00:28:15,687 --> 00:28:19,521
Yes, room 502.
I see you're staying for one night?

388
00:28:20,687 --> 00:28:25,479
And it's booked under the name…
"Xhésus Andrei."

389
00:28:25,979 --> 00:28:27,854
Yes, that's him. You have his number?

390
00:28:27,937 --> 00:28:30,687
Yes, he did leave his number,
but I can't give it out.

391
00:28:30,771 --> 00:28:33,396
- It's an emergency.
- I'm sorry, if he didn't give it to you--

392
00:28:33,479 --> 00:28:36,437
He did, but I must have saved it wrong.
It won't go through.

393
00:28:36,521 --> 00:28:39,354
[sighs] Could you check if it's the same?

394
00:28:42,062 --> 00:28:43,312
That's the number I have.

395
00:28:44,437 --> 00:28:45,937
It's not in service.

396
00:28:46,021 --> 00:28:47,896
I can't help you, I'm afraid.

397
00:28:48,729 --> 00:28:52,937
Listen, it's all paid for, everything.
Even the mini-bar and the spa.

398
00:28:58,146 --> 00:29:01,146
- [somber music playing]
- [crying]

399
00:29:10,021 --> 00:29:12,021
[sobbing]

400
00:29:27,271 --> 00:29:29,187
- [stifling tears]
- [phone ringing]

401
00:29:45,062 --> 00:29:46,062
Hello?

402
00:29:46,562 --> 00:29:47,687
[Kingsley] Hello?

403
00:29:47,771 --> 00:29:50,604
- What?
- Well, do you have the cakes?

404
00:29:51,896 --> 00:29:53,312
I will soon.

405
00:29:53,396 --> 00:29:56,021
- He's happy with the sugar?
- Yeah.

406
00:29:56,104 --> 00:29:58,521
- When's he bringing them?
- Real soon.

407
00:29:59,229 --> 00:30:01,312
- Everything good?
- Yes.

408
00:30:01,396 --> 00:30:03,812
Great. Call me when you have the cakes.

409
00:30:03,896 --> 00:30:05,146
[line disconnects]

410
00:30:05,646 --> 00:30:06,854
[cries softly]

411
00:30:11,854 --> 00:30:13,062
All right, you remember?

412
00:30:13,146 --> 00:30:16,854
Once it's sold,
log it in the ledger like Mama showed you.

413
00:30:17,437 --> 00:30:19,479
- And then?
- I write in more.

414
00:30:19,562 --> 00:30:22,271
Exactly. So someone gives you five euros…

415
00:30:22,354 --> 00:30:23,646
I put ten in the ledger.

416
00:30:23,729 --> 00:30:26,104
Don't listen to any of that, Cass.
He's feeding you bullshit.

417
00:30:26,187 --> 00:30:27,771
You could even put in 20.

418
00:30:29,146 --> 00:30:30,937
- Isn't it here?
- Oh!

419
00:30:31,021 --> 00:30:32,354
Who's this?

420
00:30:33,354 --> 00:30:34,354
[Kingsley] What the…

421
00:30:34,437 --> 00:30:37,104
These tomatoes…
Can I help you, sweetheart?

422
00:30:37,187 --> 00:30:38,437
What are you looking for?

423
00:30:38,979 --> 00:30:40,979
- I've got onions, tomatoes--
- Excuse me, ma'am.

424
00:30:41,062 --> 00:30:43,062
- You've got the wrong stand.
- The wrong stand?

425
00:30:43,146 --> 00:30:45,312
Our mother worked this spot
for over 20 years.

426
00:30:45,396 --> 00:30:47,771
Listen to me, honey,
I paid for my stand like everybody else.

427
00:30:47,854 --> 00:30:50,062
- Where even is your Mama?
- Dead and buried.

428
00:30:50,562 --> 00:30:51,646
Okay.

429
00:30:52,146 --> 00:30:54,479
And we are taking over her business.

430
00:30:54,562 --> 00:30:57,437
Well, you need to find another spot.
This one is ours now.

431
00:30:57,521 --> 00:30:59,187
THEY TOOK MAMA'S STAND
COME QUICK

432
00:30:59,271 --> 00:31:02,146
Okay, ma'am. You tried,
but we're not moving. Now get lost.

433
00:31:02,229 --> 00:31:04,771
- This is the Lafleur spot, got it?
- Wait a minute, man.

434
00:31:04,854 --> 00:31:07,021
- You best watch your mouth!
- All right, buddy. Chill.

435
00:31:07,104 --> 00:31:08,521
It's for your own good.

436
00:31:08,604 --> 00:31:10,354
Move your stuff
and pack up the shit, okay?

437
00:31:10,437 --> 00:31:12,479
- Get out of here, dumbass.
- Don't touch me, punk!

438
00:31:12,562 --> 00:31:14,396
- I said don't touch me!
- [woman] Get off him!

439
00:31:14,479 --> 00:31:15,729
Someone do something!

440
00:31:15,812 --> 00:31:17,271
- You little brat!
- [crates clatter]

441
00:31:17,354 --> 00:31:20,062
- [woman 1] Stop it! Someone grab her!
- [woman 2] What are you doing?

442
00:31:21,562 --> 00:31:23,312
- [man] Come at me!
- [blows landing]

443
00:31:23,896 --> 00:31:27,271
- [man] Yo! Knock it off! Stop!
- [woman] You're gonna pay for that!

444
00:31:27,771 --> 00:31:30,104
- [man] Come on! You want some of this?
- [Marvin] Stop!

445
00:31:30,187 --> 00:31:32,646
- [woman] Stop!
- [man] I'll kill you! You hear me?

446
00:31:33,646 --> 00:31:36,604
- [all clamoring loudly]
- Police! Police!

447
00:31:36,687 --> 00:31:39,979
Police! That's enough!
What's going on here?

448
00:31:40,062 --> 00:31:42,437
These kids here are messed up!
They attacked us!

449
00:31:42,521 --> 00:31:44,812
- [Ambre] They're squatting in our spot.
- For real.

450
00:31:44,896 --> 00:31:47,521
- [woman] We're not squatting.
- Take a breath.

451
00:31:47,604 --> 00:31:48,979
Do you have your permit on you?

452
00:31:49,062 --> 00:31:50,062
Don't have a permit,

453
00:31:50,146 --> 00:31:52,729
but our mother sold
her plants and herbs here since forever.

454
00:31:52,812 --> 00:31:54,687
Your mother was Marilyn Lafleur?

455
00:31:54,771 --> 00:31:55,896
[all] Yes.

456
00:31:57,104 --> 00:32:00,437
I remember. She was right there.
I'd come see her a lot.

457
00:32:01,896 --> 00:32:03,354
I'm very sorry for your loss.

458
00:32:04,396 --> 00:32:05,854
It's our stand.

459
00:32:06,646 --> 00:32:07,854
[crowd murmuring]

460
00:32:10,729 --> 00:32:13,354
What are you doing here?
Who said you could be here?

461
00:32:26,146 --> 00:32:27,604
Hey, may I?

462
00:32:32,062 --> 00:32:35,062
["On s'était dit" by Amah Fofana playing]

463
00:32:38,521 --> 00:32:40,312
Three days after her death.

464
00:32:40,979 --> 00:32:41,979
Nice.

465
00:32:46,979 --> 00:32:50,687
"Automatically renewable…
for three years"?

466
00:32:51,271 --> 00:32:53,437
It looks like my hands are tied.
I'm sorry.

467
00:32:53,521 --> 00:32:56,521
[somber rap song continues]

468
00:33:16,562 --> 00:33:17,562
[camera clicks]

469
00:33:33,812 --> 00:33:36,729
[somber rap song continues]

470
00:33:39,229 --> 00:33:41,604
[motorcycle approaching]

471
00:33:41,687 --> 00:33:42,729
[man 1] Yo, son.

472
00:33:42,812 --> 00:33:44,312
Damn, you gain weight again?

473
00:33:44,396 --> 00:33:47,354
[man 2] Why you gotta be so cruel?

474
00:33:47,437 --> 00:33:49,562
You think I want to be
a skinny bitch like you?

475
00:33:49,646 --> 00:33:51,979
The wind picks up, you'll blow away.

476
00:33:52,062 --> 00:33:54,021
- Yo, Fatso, what's up?
- Ain't got much time.

477
00:33:54,104 --> 00:33:55,437
Really?

478
00:33:55,521 --> 00:33:56,896
Milord's cashing in.

479
00:33:57,687 --> 00:33:59,062
- For real?
- Right now.

480
00:33:59,146 --> 00:34:03,146
Four o'clock, bring it here.
And better not tell me anything's missing.

481
00:34:03,229 --> 00:34:04,604
No sweat, I'm on it.

482
00:34:05,396 --> 00:34:06,854
All right, guys. [whistles]

483
00:34:06,937 --> 00:34:09,021
["Belle Époque"
by X-Man & Jkevlar playing]

484
00:34:09,104 --> 00:34:12,437
[dramatic rap song playing]

485
00:34:38,896 --> 00:34:40,896
[dramatic rap song continues]

486
00:35:11,354 --> 00:35:14,354
- [dramatic rap song continues]
- [inaudible]

487
00:35:41,146 --> 00:35:44,146
[dramatic rap song continues]

488
00:36:14,312 --> 00:36:16,312
[rap song fading]

489
00:36:17,729 --> 00:36:19,062
[bag unzipping]

490
00:36:30,229 --> 00:36:32,229
[indistinct chatter]

491
00:36:40,896 --> 00:36:44,479
- [car starting]
- It's like being on a vacation kinda, but…

492
00:36:44,562 --> 00:36:46,146
- Shorter.
- Smaller, yeah.

493
00:36:46,229 --> 00:36:47,229
Shorter.

494
00:36:47,729 --> 00:36:49,062
Got a girlfriend?

495
00:36:50,437 --> 00:36:52,396
Mmm, nah, don't have time for that.

496
00:36:52,479 --> 00:36:53,854
Why, want to be my girl?

497
00:36:54,354 --> 00:36:55,437
Pfft, don't be silly.

498
00:36:55,521 --> 00:36:56,604
[woman] Maeva?

499
00:36:57,229 --> 00:36:59,562
Okay. See ya, man.

500
00:36:59,646 --> 00:37:00,854
[Léo] See ya tomorrow.

501
00:37:09,354 --> 00:37:10,729
[SherKhan] Casanova.

502
00:37:11,604 --> 00:37:12,896
Who's that, your chick?

503
00:37:14,021 --> 00:37:16,104
You an actor? Saw your little movie.

504
00:37:17,937 --> 00:37:19,271
"We're inadmissible."

505
00:37:19,771 --> 00:37:22,062
[imitates gun firing and chuckles]

506
00:37:23,562 --> 00:37:24,854
All right, let's do this.

507
00:37:25,354 --> 00:37:26,396
Get in.

508
00:37:28,521 --> 00:37:30,271
Hurry up. Get in, now.

509
00:37:54,562 --> 00:37:55,729
You know who I am?

510
00:37:56,604 --> 00:37:59,229
SherKhan. You're the boss in Trénelle.

511
00:38:00,021 --> 00:38:01,562
I'm the boss everywhere.

512
00:38:04,687 --> 00:38:05,687
Where you from?

513
00:38:06,187 --> 00:38:08,021
What the fuck do you care?

514
00:38:09,396 --> 00:38:10,521
[laughs softly]

515
00:38:11,312 --> 00:38:12,479
We got a badass.

516
00:38:12,562 --> 00:38:14,604
Want to be a badass?
Want to be a badass, kid?

517
00:38:14,687 --> 00:38:17,312
So why'd you say "in the mouth"
in your videos, punk?

518
00:38:21,104 --> 00:38:22,812
Answer me, bitch.

519
00:38:23,771 --> 00:38:26,437
You're not gonna kill me, man.
It's disproportionate.

520
00:38:26,521 --> 00:38:28,979
[laughing]

521
00:38:29,062 --> 00:38:32,021
How 'bout I just shoot you
in your knee, then? Is that proportionate?

522
00:38:32,937 --> 00:38:35,604
Answer me or I'll blow your leg off!

523
00:38:35,687 --> 00:38:38,437
I… tried to impress my friends.

524
00:38:38,521 --> 00:38:41,021
Your friends?
Are you fucking with me, kid?

525
00:38:41,104 --> 00:38:42,604
No, I swear, I was making it all up.

526
00:38:42,687 --> 00:38:43,979
Look at this gun.

527
00:38:44,479 --> 00:38:47,521
It's gonna be so damn loud!
You have no idea how much it'll bleed.

528
00:38:47,604 --> 00:38:49,562
You'll have a giant hole.
Is that what you want?

529
00:38:50,854 --> 00:38:52,812
I promise it's the truth. I want my mama.

530
00:39:00,896 --> 00:39:02,896
You're one of them Lafleurs, huh?

531
00:39:10,729 --> 00:39:12,146
All right, get out, punk.

532
00:39:12,979 --> 00:39:13,812
Move.

533
00:39:17,437 --> 00:39:20,646
[softly] Go fuck yourself, SherKhan.
You and your stupid Glock.

534
00:39:28,521 --> 00:39:30,521
[Kylian sighs]

535
00:39:44,229 --> 00:39:45,062
What's going on?

536
00:39:46,437 --> 00:39:47,646
That punk-ass bitch.

537
00:39:49,354 --> 00:39:50,812
That's the harvest?

538
00:39:51,646 --> 00:39:53,854
No. It's our reserves.

539
00:39:54,854 --> 00:39:56,312
Sentinel's disappeared.

540
00:39:56,396 --> 00:39:58,021
With the harvest?

541
00:39:58,937 --> 00:40:00,187
[Fatso] Seems so.

542
00:40:01,812 --> 00:40:03,229
[exhales deeply]

543
00:40:04,312 --> 00:40:05,521
You called him, right?

544
00:40:05,604 --> 00:40:07,521
Only ten million times.

545
00:40:07,604 --> 00:40:09,062
Fuck.

546
00:40:10,854 --> 00:40:11,687
[sighs]

547
00:40:12,437 --> 00:40:13,646
We will find him.

548
00:40:14,146 --> 00:40:17,062
Before tomorrow? Where's he live?

549
00:40:23,229 --> 00:40:24,229
[sighs]

550
00:40:26,646 --> 00:40:28,937
I think he stays with his mother
when she's on vacation.

551
00:40:33,187 --> 00:40:35,187
[suspenseful music playing]

552
00:41:17,687 --> 00:41:20,146
[suspenseful music continues]

553
00:41:45,187 --> 00:41:47,187
[suspenseful music building]

554
00:42:00,854 --> 00:42:02,354
[Fatso] Yo, what up, boss?

555
00:42:05,604 --> 00:42:06,729
You fucked up, son.

556
00:42:10,979 --> 00:42:12,771
Sick of your shit!
I'll fucking take it all!

557
00:42:14,854 --> 00:42:15,854
Sébastien!

558
00:42:15,937 --> 00:42:17,771
Told you, stay in your room, God damn!

559
00:42:18,896 --> 00:42:19,896
Drop it!

560
00:42:21,437 --> 00:42:22,479
[pleading] We tried.

561
00:42:22,562 --> 00:42:24,187
It… It didn't work.

562
00:42:24,271 --> 00:42:25,729
Please, drop it.

563
00:42:31,562 --> 00:42:34,187
[suspenseful music continues]

564
00:42:37,854 --> 00:42:40,187
Okay, guys. I'm sorry.

565
00:42:41,562 --> 00:42:43,271
Shit. God damn it.

566
00:42:46,021 --> 00:42:47,937
I'm sorry, guys. I fucked up.

567
00:42:50,146 --> 00:42:51,896
I needed money for my baby. I panicked.

568
00:42:52,562 --> 00:42:53,979
I'll pay it all back with interest.

569
00:42:54,854 --> 00:42:55,854
You're sorry?

570
00:42:55,937 --> 00:42:57,062
Sorry, Milord.

571
00:43:07,979 --> 00:43:09,646
He's sorry, guys.

572
00:43:10,896 --> 00:43:12,604
You don't have to kill him.

573
00:43:13,937 --> 00:43:15,312
[sighs]

574
00:43:23,896 --> 00:43:26,896
- [door closing in background]
- [Sentinel groaning]

575
00:43:29,479 --> 00:43:30,687
[woman] Stop it, please!

576
00:43:33,979 --> 00:43:36,979
- [groaning continues]
- ["Mozart" by Mercenaire playing]

577
00:43:40,312 --> 00:43:43,312
["Mozart" continues playing]

578
00:44:49,771 --> 00:44:52,771
["Saydia" by Marginal playing]

579
00:45:02,937 --> 00:45:05,437
- Whoa!
- [cars honking]

580
00:45:07,229 --> 00:45:10,229
["Saydia" continues playing]

581
00:45:16,229 --> 00:45:19,229
- [shower running]
- ["Saydia" continues playing]

582
00:45:32,521 --> 00:45:35,521
[song fading into background]

583
00:45:51,312 --> 00:45:53,312
[line ringing]

584
00:45:54,937 --> 00:45:56,146
[Kingsley] Hey, Belle.

585
00:45:57,812 --> 00:46:00,729
- Hello? You good?
- No, King, I'm real bad.

586
00:46:00,812 --> 00:46:01,937
What's going on?

587
00:46:03,771 --> 00:46:04,771
Tell me.

588
00:46:06,271 --> 00:46:09,146
He screwed me. He left me.
He told me he'd come back.

589
00:46:09,229 --> 00:46:11,312
- What?
- And I listened.

590
00:46:14,062 --> 00:46:15,771
He gave me a fake number.

591
00:46:16,562 --> 00:46:17,812
I'm in deep shit.

592
00:46:17,896 --> 00:46:19,312
- [exhales]
- Tell me everything.

593
00:46:19,396 --> 00:46:21,521
What the fuck are you talking about?

594
00:46:23,146 --> 00:46:24,437
[voice breaking] Xhésus.

595
00:46:25,771 --> 00:46:27,146
He disappeared.

596
00:46:27,646 --> 00:46:29,229
What the fuck are you saying?

597
00:46:29,312 --> 00:46:30,604
I'm fucked.

598
00:46:30,687 --> 00:46:31,937
Wait, wait, wait.

599
00:46:32,021 --> 00:46:36,146
But where are the cakes?
Annabelle, answer me.

600
00:46:36,687 --> 00:46:38,062
They're with him.

601
00:46:38,146 --> 00:46:40,646
What? You let him take the cakes?

602
00:46:40,729 --> 00:46:42,937
What is wrong with you? Are you nuts?

603
00:46:43,021 --> 00:46:45,021
- [knock on door]
- Why didn't you tell me earlier?

604
00:46:45,104 --> 00:46:48,021
- Now it's too late. You fucked up.
- King, hold on a second.

605
00:46:48,104 --> 00:46:50,312
[faintly] Hold on?
What do you mean, hold on?

606
00:46:50,396 --> 00:46:52,479
Yo, what's going on? Hello?

607
00:46:52,562 --> 00:46:54,854
Hello? Hello, Belle?

608
00:46:56,021 --> 00:46:57,812
Hello? Come on, answer me!

609
00:46:57,896 --> 00:46:59,812
King, it's him. Call you back.

610
00:46:59,896 --> 00:47:01,229
What's happening? I--

611
00:47:02,396 --> 00:47:04,687
[breathes deeply]

612
00:47:08,854 --> 00:47:10,062
You got it?

613
00:47:18,646 --> 00:47:19,854
[door closes]

614
00:47:33,021 --> 00:47:34,062
You okay?

615
00:47:35,604 --> 00:47:36,979
You gave me a fake number!

616
00:47:37,062 --> 00:47:40,396
I shut my phone off. I always do that.
It makes it harder to be traced.

617
00:47:40,979 --> 00:47:42,146
Why didn't you tell me?

618
00:47:42,229 --> 00:47:43,604
I'm sorry. Really.

619
00:47:44,187 --> 00:47:45,896
It took longer than I expected.

620
00:47:47,437 --> 00:47:49,312
I thought you were enjoying the pool.

621
00:47:50,687 --> 00:47:51,687
Didn't you check it out?

622
00:47:52,812 --> 00:47:53,937
What about the spa?

623
00:47:57,062 --> 00:47:58,062
Shit.

624
00:47:58,896 --> 00:47:59,896
This sucks.

625
00:48:05,521 --> 00:48:06,771
Come here.

626
00:48:08,187 --> 00:48:09,437
[Annabelle crying softly]

627
00:48:12,854 --> 00:48:13,937
I'm so sorry.

628
00:48:14,521 --> 00:48:15,854
I thought you trusted me.

629
00:48:15,937 --> 00:48:17,812
[Annabelle sobs] Yeah, you wish.

630
00:48:36,229 --> 00:48:38,729
- [motorcycle revving]
- Whoo!

631
00:48:40,396 --> 00:48:41,437
Yes!

632
00:48:41,521 --> 00:48:44,062
- [exhales]
- ["Si Balan" by Shannon playing]

633
00:48:54,479 --> 00:48:57,479
["Si Balan" continues playing]

634
00:49:01,062 --> 00:49:02,104
Yo, dude.

635
00:49:02,604 --> 00:49:03,896
[Kingsley] Yo, what up?

636
00:49:05,187 --> 00:49:07,396
- What's good? How you doing?
- Oh, you know.

637
00:49:08,271 --> 00:49:09,229
Hey.

638
00:49:10,562 --> 00:49:11,771
Nice ride.

639
00:49:12,979 --> 00:49:14,812
- Here.
- Thanks, bro.

640
00:49:22,354 --> 00:49:24,812
- [Kingsley] Yeah.
- That Margot from Instagram?

641
00:49:25,312 --> 00:49:26,937
Come on, you know.

642
00:49:28,104 --> 00:49:30,104
["Si Balan" continues playing]

643
00:49:34,896 --> 00:49:36,896
[bikes revving]

644
00:49:50,354 --> 00:49:53,354
- [indistinct chatter]
- [rap song continues]

645
00:49:56,646 --> 00:49:59,646
[indistinct hushed chatter]

646
00:49:59,729 --> 00:50:02,312
[hushed chatter continues]

647
00:50:06,521 --> 00:50:08,021
Give us a sec.

648
00:50:10,062 --> 00:50:11,604
- Khan.
- Hmm?

649
00:50:11,687 --> 00:50:15,937
You mentioned some guys from Saint-Joseph.
You see him there?

650
00:50:16,562 --> 00:50:18,521
He's from Saint-Joseph.

651
00:50:18,604 --> 00:50:20,854
Name's Kingsley Lafleur.

652
00:50:21,812 --> 00:50:23,021
How'd you find that out?

653
00:50:24,229 --> 00:50:26,604
The Snoop. He told me.

654
00:50:32,729 --> 00:50:34,312
Go bring him here.

655
00:50:37,562 --> 00:50:40,396
[engines revving loudly]

656
00:50:53,729 --> 00:50:55,729
[indistinct chatter]

657
00:50:55,812 --> 00:50:57,354
SherKhan wants to see you.

658
00:50:57,437 --> 00:50:59,271
SherKhan? Who's that?

659
00:51:07,937 --> 00:51:10,187
- You're blocking the view.
- [laughs]

660
00:51:12,604 --> 00:51:15,479
Got a perfect eyeline.
He can see me from there.

661
00:51:16,271 --> 00:51:18,604
If he's got something to say,
he can come here.

662
00:51:25,604 --> 00:51:26,604
[blows kiss]

663
00:51:26,687 --> 00:51:28,687
[rap song continues]

664
00:51:31,854 --> 00:51:32,854
[Kingsley] Anyway.

665
00:51:41,521 --> 00:51:43,479
He's being disrespectful.

666
00:51:44,271 --> 00:51:45,479
For real.

667
00:51:46,354 --> 00:51:48,271
Needs to be taken down a peg.

668
00:52:19,771 --> 00:52:21,646
[menacing music playing]

669
00:52:30,146 --> 00:52:31,479
[tires screeching]

670
00:52:32,229 --> 00:52:35,229
- Hold on tight!
- [menacing music continues]

671
00:52:57,229 --> 00:52:58,521
[SherKhan] Hey, Lafleur!

672
00:53:03,146 --> 00:53:05,062
Let me get off, King!

673
00:53:05,562 --> 00:53:07,562
- [car horn blaring]
- [tires squealing]

674
00:53:09,562 --> 00:53:10,937
Yo, move! Fuck!

675
00:53:15,562 --> 00:53:17,312
[SherKhan] I'm gonna rip your head off!

676
00:53:27,396 --> 00:53:29,771
Lafleur! You're fucking dead!

677
00:53:35,562 --> 00:53:37,562
[menacing music continues]

678
00:53:52,812 --> 00:53:55,812
- [bike driving off]
- [music fading]

679
00:54:01,854 --> 00:54:04,687
If I tell you I want to get off,
you let me off, asshole.

680
00:54:04,771 --> 00:54:07,479
You see that guy?
If I let you off, you'd be dead.

681
00:54:07,562 --> 00:54:09,604
He'd have killed you.
I saved your life, you know.

682
00:54:09,687 --> 00:54:12,521
SherKhan? Ha! I would eat him alive.

683
00:54:18,062 --> 00:54:19,062
Mmm-mmm.

684
00:54:19,646 --> 00:54:20,896
You want another?

685
00:54:29,021 --> 00:54:31,021
[dark music playing]

686
00:54:33,437 --> 00:54:36,396
He's called Kingsley Lafleur.
A little bitch from Saint-Joseph.

687
00:54:36,479 --> 00:54:38,521
This bro's got it fucking coming!
I'm not playing.

688
00:54:38,604 --> 00:54:40,312
Whoever gets him, ten grand.

689
00:54:40,396 --> 00:54:43,187
I want this bitch found.
Y'all find him right now.

690
00:54:44,937 --> 00:54:47,937
[darkly intriguing music playing]

691
00:55:22,437 --> 00:55:23,604
[Kylian] SherKhan.

692
00:55:23,687 --> 00:55:25,146
Yo, prove that it's you.

693
00:55:25,646 --> 00:55:26,854
[Kylian] Doesn't matter.

694
00:55:26,937 --> 00:55:28,229
Listen carefully.

695
00:55:28,312 --> 00:55:30,396
- You're messing up our business.
- Hmm?

696
00:55:31,354 --> 00:55:32,729
You heard me.

697
00:55:32,812 --> 00:55:35,979
That video's gone viral.
It's already in the prefect's office.

698
00:55:37,479 --> 00:55:38,896
So listen good.

699
00:55:38,979 --> 00:55:40,187
I have your dope.

700
00:55:40,687 --> 00:55:41,687
Hold on.

701
00:55:41,771 --> 00:55:44,979
- You stole from me, Milord?
- Calm down, SherKhan.

702
00:55:45,062 --> 00:55:46,896
- That's not my style.
- Oh, I'mma calm down.

703
00:55:46,979 --> 00:55:49,979
I'm gonna butcher you.
That'll calm me down and then some.

704
00:55:50,479 --> 00:55:53,521
[Kylian] You're not crazy.
Your dope's being sold in Paris.

705
00:55:53,604 --> 00:55:55,937
It'll bring in 400,000 euros, I guarantee.

706
00:55:56,521 --> 00:55:58,271
One week, and it's yours.
On one condition.

707
00:55:58,354 --> 00:56:02,229
Oh, you fucking nuts!
You negotiating with my own merchandise?

708
00:56:02,771 --> 00:56:04,021
You smoking crack?

709
00:56:04,104 --> 00:56:07,271
Your dumb little video
got the attention of the authorities.

710
00:56:07,771 --> 00:56:09,521
All cause you had to be a child.

711
00:56:10,021 --> 00:56:12,687
Oh, come on.
Say this to my face, Milord, I dare you.

712
00:56:13,187 --> 00:56:14,812
[Kylian] So here's our new deal.

713
00:56:14,896 --> 00:56:17,812
You take what we offer you
and leave the Lafleur kid alone.

714
00:56:18,396 --> 00:56:20,229
- And as a deposit…
- Yo.

715
00:56:23,021 --> 00:56:24,437
[rooster crowing]

716
00:56:24,521 --> 00:56:25,729
[car alarm chirps]

717
00:56:29,104 --> 00:56:31,729
- Why are you protecting him?
- I'm protecting my business.

718
00:56:31,812 --> 00:56:34,521
Yours as well.
Keep your phone on. I'll be in touch.

719
00:56:35,687 --> 00:56:38,937
- And call off the hit on the Lafleur kid.
- And if I refuse?

720
00:56:39,021 --> 00:56:40,437
[call disconnects]

721
00:56:51,146 --> 00:56:53,146
[bikes revving]

722
00:56:58,812 --> 00:57:01,812
[bikes riding off]

723
00:57:04,479 --> 00:57:05,479
[sighs]

724
00:57:20,312 --> 00:57:22,104
I've collected it all.

725
00:57:22,687 --> 00:57:24,479
Deposit of 64,000.

726
00:57:24,562 --> 00:57:25,729
Like you asked.

727
00:57:41,354 --> 00:57:45,354
I'll send you the time, the date,
and the location of the delivery.

728
00:57:45,437 --> 00:57:47,312
Keep yourself alive till then.

729
00:57:51,437 --> 00:57:53,437
[engine revving]

730
00:58:04,354 --> 00:58:07,354
["PLP VME" by Lé Will & Deuspi playing]

731
00:58:19,687 --> 00:58:21,312
[phone buzzing]

732
00:58:21,396 --> 00:58:22,812
We in business.

733
00:58:22,896 --> 00:58:24,896
[man laughing]

734
00:58:27,729 --> 00:58:30,521
JC - I warned you.
It's over. Forget about me.

735
00:58:33,562 --> 00:58:36,104
["PLP VME" continues playing]

736
00:58:43,021 --> 00:58:46,021
["PLP VME" continues playing]

737
00:59:12,146 --> 00:59:15,146
[dramatic rap song continues playing]
